==English==

===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|en|En-au-whistle in the dark.ogg|Audio (AU)}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|*}}

# {{lb|en|colloquial}} To make a show of [[bravery]] despite one's fears; to [[put on a brave face]].
#* '''2011''', {{w|Norman Davies}}, ''Vanished Kingdoms'', Penguin 2012, p. 6:
#*: Those who seriously believe ‘There'll always be an England’ are '''whistling in the dark'''.
# {{lb|en|idiomatic|US}} To speak of something despite having little [[knowledge]] of it.

